cs.NE, cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.ET

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper is about training deep neural networks using a new number system. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the paper proposes an efficient hardware architecture for the posit multiply-and-accumulate operation. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another likely category as the paper demonstrates the successful training of DNN models on ImageNet image classification task. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category as the paper discusses the computational complexity of DNN models and proposes a solution for efficient DNN implementations. 
- cs.ET (Embedded Systems) is another possible category as the proposed hardware architecture is aimed at low-power DNN training accelerators.
